WEBVTT

00:02.300 --> 00:04.180
♪ <i>MTV.</i>♪

00:04.380 --> 00:10.010
<i>[marching drum plays]</i>

00:25.800 --> 00:27.720
[stirrups jangling]

00:38.340 --> 00:39.570
Steady!

00:39.760 --> 00:42.250
[drumming stops]

00:47.390 --> 00:48.700
[gunshot]

00:49.700 --> 00:51.400
[clamoring]

00:51.600 --> 00:54.090
- [cannons firing]
- Hold the line!

01:10.200 --> 01:11.200
[horse squeals]

01:14.770 --> 01:16.110
[neighs]

01:18.860 --> 01:21.730
Hold that line! Hold the line!

01:32.650 --> 01:34.230
Hold the line!

01:34.430 --> 01:35.440
[clamoring]

01:37.610 --> 01:39.360
Hold the line!

01:46.840 --> 01:49.640
Brave men of the 11th!

01:49.830 --> 01:52.200
Get together, God damn!

01:52.400 --> 01:55.420
[explosions continue]

01:55.620 --> 01:58.640
Theirs not to make reply!

01:58.840 --> 02:01.210
Theirs not to reason why!

02:01.410 --> 02:04.640
Theirs but to do and die!

02:07.470 --> 02:09.220
You will follow me,

02:09.420 --> 02:10.650
and you will fire.

02:13.260 --> 02:15.220
Charge!

02:34.280 --> 02:35.320
[yells]

02:43.850 --> 02:46.130
<i>♪ suspenseful music </i>

02:46.330 --> 02:48.770
<i>♪♪♪</i>

03:12.710 --> 03:14.150
Fire!

03:14.350 --> 03:16.190
<i>♪♪♪</i>

03:19.540 --> 03:20.810
Advance!

03:21.010 --> 03:23.730
[troops shouting]

03:23.930 --> 03:26.460
[troops chanting]

03:28.420 --> 03:32.340
[men shouting rebel yell]

03:42.300 --> 03:44.620
<i>♪ dramatic music </i>

03:44.820 --> 03:47.310
<i>♪♪♪</i>

03:48.310 --> 03:50.310
[horse neighs]

04:15.820 --> 04:18.640
[screams]

04:21.470 --> 04:24.390
[whooping]

04:27.700 --> 04:29.880
<i>♪ atmospheric music </i>

04:30.080 --> 04:33.440
<i>♪♪♪</i>

04:35.440 --> 04:37.490
<i>♪♪♪</i>

04:57.380 --> 05:00.430
<i>♪♪♪</i>

05:41.600 --> 05:43.820
[groaning]

05:48.730 --> 05:50.910
[excited chatter]

06:11.450 --> 06:13.540
You done killed the wrong side.

06:14.720 --> 06:16.590
I'd rather be shot in the face
than in the back.

06:24.030 --> 06:26.960
[man]
We collected 200 prisoners

06:27.160 --> 06:29.040
and a battery of field guns...

06:29.240 --> 06:31.000
[cheering]

06:31.200 --> 06:35.360
...while McCulloch's division
suffered 325 casualties,

06:35.560 --> 06:39.840
with 788 unaccounted for,

06:40.040 --> 06:43.360
thought to be killed, deserted

06:43.560 --> 06:45.450
or runaway.

06:45.650 --> 06:47.450
Another challenge
in this bloody campaign

06:47.650 --> 06:49.460
we must overcome.

06:49.660 --> 06:51.980
There's nothing we can't,
nothing we won't,

06:52.180 --> 06:54.640
for God favors the Confederacy.

06:54.840 --> 06:55.720
[murmurs of agreement]

06:55.920 --> 06:57.550
Let us adjourn, gentlemen.

06:57.750 --> 06:59.850
No war has ever been won
on an empty belly.

07:01.500 --> 07:04.860
Before dinner, sir,
if you don't mind...

07:05.060 --> 07:07.820
inform us when
the supply train will arrive.

07:08.020 --> 07:10.520
Has it not arrived?

07:10.720 --> 07:13.610
I'm not aware of it, General.

07:13.810 --> 07:17.790
Despite good counsel
from many honorable men here,

07:17.990 --> 07:20.920
you made the decision
to leave our wagons behind

07:21.120 --> 07:24.670
to advantage our swift flight
and goal of surprise.

07:24.870 --> 07:28.930
We marched fast, only to
find ourselves outflanked,

07:29.130 --> 07:31.720
outmaneuvered and now,
out-supplied.

07:31.920 --> 07:34.110
Major, that may be
an unfortunate oversight.

07:34.310 --> 07:36.110
My oversight, indeed.

07:36.310 --> 07:38.510
Yes, General, yours indeed.

07:38.710 --> 07:39.420
[murmuring]

07:39.620 --> 07:41.030
Are you finished?

07:41.230 --> 07:42.730
<i>♪ quiet, dramatic music </i>

07:42.930 --> 07:45.510
[George] I hear that you like
poetry, is that right?

07:45.710 --> 07:47.860
[Van Dorn]
A poet typically does, Major.

07:48.060 --> 07:49.860
[men chuckling]

07:50.060 --> 07:51.820
Thank you.

07:52.020 --> 07:53.950
[Van Dorn] What is your
current line of inquiry...

07:55.820 --> 07:57.520
I saw you.

07:59.690 --> 08:01.700
What is your name, soldier?

08:01.900 --> 08:04.490
No soldier, sir.

08:04.690 --> 08:05.880
Just Bass.

08:06.080 --> 08:08.610
Well, you are
a wolf, then, Bass.

08:10.050 --> 08:12.670
We are a breed apart.

08:12.870 --> 08:13.930
We know our own.

08:14.130 --> 08:16.630
<i>♪♪♪</i>

08:16.830 --> 08:18.760
[George] "...and the lovely
plumage of the bird's

08:18.960 --> 08:20.810
that never alights;

08:21.010 --> 08:23.590
less celestial,

08:23.790 --> 08:26.770
I celebrate a tail."

08:26.970 --> 08:29.640
As do I, gentlemen.

08:29.840 --> 08:33.120
Consider yourself
dismissed, Major.

08:39.690 --> 08:40.990
Bass.

08:44.650 --> 08:46.700
<i>♪♪♪</i>

08:49.090 --> 08:50.610
[door closes]

08:55.010 --> 08:58.800
It's a damn confederacy
of dunces, Bass.

08:59.000 --> 09:01.150
It's not debatable, is it?

09:01.350 --> 09:02.550
No, sir.

09:02.750 --> 09:04.760
"No, sir," indeed.

09:06.190 --> 09:09.770
Strike my tent. Pack my gear.

09:09.970 --> 09:11.810
Tack the horses.

09:19.770 --> 09:21.700
<i>♪ slow, dramatic music </i>

09:21.900 --> 09:23.560
<i>♪♪♪</i>

09:47.890 --> 09:49.150
[flies buzzing]

09:50.890 --> 09:52.850
<i>♪♪♪</i>

10:07.730 --> 10:10.040
Where do you think you're
headed, Mr. Nighttime?

10:13.740 --> 10:16.790
To get the horses a little
of that grass over yonder.

10:16.990 --> 10:19.930
My Henry rifle
may have served you well,

10:20.130 --> 10:22.050
but don't go thinking
you're any kind of master now.

10:25.360 --> 10:29.280
Boy, I don't think I cotton
to the light in your eyes.

10:29.480 --> 10:31.110
Answer me straight.

10:31.310 --> 10:33.940
Do you mistake me for
some kind of cowardly deserter?

10:34.140 --> 10:35.680
No, sir.

10:35.880 --> 10:38.640
You Master Reeves,
through and through.

10:38.840 --> 10:41.210
I received dispensation
from Van Dorn.

10:41.410 --> 10:44.780
"Damn Born's" more like it.

10:44.980 --> 10:46.690
He's calling it
a health reprieve.

10:46.890 --> 10:48.780
Pardon my saying, sir,

10:48.980 --> 10:51.790
but you didn't fight
like no sick man.

10:51.990 --> 10:55.270
Well, I suspect he was
sick of my company, Bass.

10:55.470 --> 10:58.230
Mutual sentiment to be sure.

10:58.430 --> 10:59.840
Can't figure how the general

11:00.040 --> 11:01.880
didn't find you
sweet like honey.

11:02.080 --> 11:04.060
I did leave him
a bit stung, didn't I?

11:04.260 --> 11:05.840
Deep, I'd say.

11:06.040 --> 11:08.790
[chuckles]

11:12.100 --> 11:13.630
Go get your grass.

11:13.830 --> 11:15.760
Yes, sir.

11:35.910 --> 11:38.830
Don't think you're going to
sleep while I lie here awake.

11:39.030 --> 11:41.310
Oh, no, sir.

11:41.510 --> 11:44.750
Just admiring God's creation.

11:44.950 --> 11:47.790
You ever thought God could be
our own creation instead?

11:48.790 --> 11:50.150
No, sir.

11:50.350 --> 11:51.750
Well, isn't that rich?

11:54.140 --> 11:55.720
If you could read,

11:55.920 --> 11:57.760
you'd surely delight
in Longfellow.

11:58.840 --> 12:01.810
Who knows,
you two could be right,

12:02.010 --> 12:04.730
there could be life after.

12:04.930 --> 12:06.950
Some grand paradise above.

12:07.150 --> 12:09.820
I'd still like to learn, Master.

12:10.020 --> 12:11.910
So I could study the Bible.

12:12.110 --> 12:13.910
You're not thinking

12:14.110 --> 12:15.990
niggers go to the good part
of Heaven, are you?

12:16.990 --> 12:17.860
Sir?

12:21.950 --> 12:24.830
You see that big
separation up there?

12:26.260 --> 12:28.740
You're looking at all
the pretty twinkling lights.

12:30.530 --> 12:33.060
But if you're going anywhere,

12:33.260 --> 12:35.010
you're going
to where there's nothing.

12:36.140 --> 12:38.410
Just black airy nothing.

12:38.610 --> 12:41.720
That part
you ain't even looking at.

12:41.920 --> 12:44.770
Only white folks
go to the big dance, boy.

12:44.970 --> 12:46.860
If anybody's going anywhere.

12:47.060 --> 12:48.860
<i>♪ soft, dramatic music </i>

12:49.060 --> 12:50.940
<i>♪♪♪</i>

12:54.460 --> 12:57.030
Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa.

12:59.120 --> 13:01.820
This is an unusual conservation.

13:11.090 --> 13:13.100
Wait here.

13:13.300 --> 13:15.050
Yes, sir.

13:25.150 --> 13:26.890
Rachel?

13:29.930 --> 13:31.030
Rachel?

13:31.230 --> 13:32.810
<i>♪♪♪</i>

13:37.900 --> 13:39.470
Nobody's here.

13:40.600 --> 13:41.900
No, sir?

13:51.090 --> 13:54.790
When you finish up,
come find me.

13:54.990 --> 13:56.090
Yes, sir.

14:02.010 --> 14:04.490
No garlands, no trumpets.

14:06.010 --> 14:08.060
Just us tonight.

14:10.190 --> 14:11.850
Such a sad homecoming.

14:23.990 --> 14:26.510
[insects trilling]

15:00.370 --> 15:01.980
Jennie?

15:13.040 --> 15:15.000
Is it you?

15:16.210 --> 15:17.430
It is.

15:21.050 --> 15:22.930
<i>♪ gentle music </i>

15:23.130 --> 15:25.090
<i>♪♪♪</i>

15:45.330 --> 15:47.200
Is the war over?

15:48.420 --> 15:51.000
It is for me.

15:51.200 --> 15:52.470
[sighs]

15:55.120 --> 15:57.520
<i>♪♪♪</i>

16:23.540 --> 16:26.590
<i>♪♪♪</i>

16:53.830 --> 16:55.540
[George]
Bass!

16:55.740 --> 16:57.840
God damn you.

17:00.580 --> 17:02.100
Bass!

17:03.890 --> 17:05.890
That man just can't quit you.

17:08.020 --> 17:10.590
Want me to tell him
that I'm yours tonight?

17:13.980 --> 17:15.550
You mine forever.

17:41.400 --> 17:42.750
Master?

17:47.280 --> 17:48.810
Master Reeves?

17:49.010 --> 17:50.190
You there?

18:02.730 --> 18:04.260
Master, you in there?

18:04.460 --> 18:06.040
[George]
You found me.

18:07.820 --> 18:09.530
You want me to come in?

18:09.730 --> 18:11.780
I said, "You found me."

18:22.100 --> 18:23.890
Do you know what
I've been ruminating on

18:24.090 --> 18:26.670
this whole time you were
tending to the horses?

18:26.870 --> 18:29.540
Or doing whatever else
took you so damn long?

18:31.280 --> 18:33.940
I was thinking,

18:34.140 --> 18:36.950
"Watch.

18:37.150 --> 18:40.080
That nigger will run off

18:40.280 --> 18:44.210
before I give him a chance
to walk away scot-free."

18:47.600 --> 18:48.640
Master?

18:52.260 --> 18:55.830
The whole damn family
is visiting Rachel's folks.

18:56.030 --> 18:58.130
Ain't that
some unlucky bullshit?

19:00.000 --> 19:02.880
Now, we could ride over there
and rouse them one and all.

19:04.270 --> 19:06.180
A merry ruckus.

19:07.840 --> 19:10.980
Or we could share
a gentler repast here,

19:11.180 --> 19:13.230
play a round of cards.

19:15.500 --> 19:16.900
Yes, sir.

19:17.100 --> 19:18.160
That's it?

19:18.360 --> 19:19.950
That's all you got to say to me?

19:20.140 --> 19:21.850
Thank you, Master.

19:23.330 --> 19:27.130
You act as though you don't
believe I'm a man of my word.

19:27.330 --> 19:28.560
Oh, no.

19:28.760 --> 19:31.000
I'm listening.
I'm listening, sir.

19:31.200 --> 19:33.610
Confused, but listening.

19:33.810 --> 19:35.700
So, how am I confusing you, boy?

19:35.900 --> 19:38.050
No, sir, I'm not saying
you're confusing me.

19:38.250 --> 19:40.230
I'm saying I'm-I'm
confused all on my own

19:40.430 --> 19:42.790
about how I can
walk out of here scot-free.

19:42.990 --> 19:44.140
Here's my offer.

19:44.340 --> 19:46.150
You only get one chance,

19:46.350 --> 19:47.710
fleeting and final.

19:47.910 --> 19:49.840
War is war that way,
and this is war.

19:51.750 --> 19:55.110
After your heroics in battle,

19:55.310 --> 19:57.190
this is what I'll do.

19:58.930 --> 20:01.060
I'll set you free tonight.

20:02.370 --> 20:04.640
I'll write out
a letter of manumission

20:04.840 --> 20:06.720
you can carry with you
at all times.

20:08.250 --> 20:10.330
That's my promise.

20:11.340 --> 20:13.080
That sound awful kind.

20:20.130 --> 20:21.650
But you must beat your master.

20:24.260 --> 20:25.970
<i>♪ tense, dramatic music </i>

20:26.170 --> 20:27.870
<i>♪♪♪</i>

20:52.330 --> 20:53.810
Hurry up.

20:54.420 --> 20:55.810
Yes, sir.

21:07.350 --> 21:10.000
You're counting, boy.
I can see your lips move.

21:11.220 --> 21:13.150
Sorry, sir. I-I got to.

21:13.350 --> 21:15.530
Jesus.

21:17.620 --> 21:19.240
- I can't draw until you do.
- Yes, sir.

21:19.440 --> 21:20.360
I'm hurrying.

21:29.630 --> 21:30.900
You ready now?

21:31.100 --> 21:32.850
Ready, Master.

21:35.940 --> 21:37.250
Almost perfect, is it?

21:53.260 --> 21:55.450
My hand's not bad either.

21:55.650 --> 21:57.320
<i>♪ tense, dramatic music </i>

21:57.520 --> 21:59.400
<i>♪♪♪</i>

22:02.100 --> 22:03.320
You look first.

22:10.410 --> 22:11.930
Yes, sir.

22:26.860 --> 22:28.470
<i>♪♪♪</i>

22:36.350 --> 22:38.530
[chuckles] Yeah.

22:39.660 --> 22:41.270
[giggles]

22:42.530 --> 22:45.370
Oh, your God
has been good to me.

22:45.570 --> 22:46.800
[drink pours]

22:48.320 --> 22:51.100
Let's see what lot
He has given you.

22:56.460 --> 22:59.500
<i>♪♪♪</i>

23:09.470 --> 23:11.820
Well, that can't be, boy.

23:12.600 --> 23:14.530
Do you realize what you have?

23:14.730 --> 23:16.430
A plain flush?

23:19.520 --> 23:21.570
I must congratulate you.

23:23.440 --> 23:25.090
[sniffles]

23:26.570 --> 23:28.800
That beats a lot of hands.

23:29.000 --> 23:32.200
A pair, two pair,
three of a kind, a straight.

23:32.400 --> 23:34.930
But it doesn't
beat a full house.

23:36.150 --> 23:39.380
And it doesn't beat...

23:39.580 --> 23:41.500
four of a kind.

23:49.340 --> 23:50.990
Ooh, that was a close one.

23:52.250 --> 23:53.390
You-you don't play poker

23:53.590 --> 23:55.390
like I taught you
to shoot them Yankees,

23:55.590 --> 23:56.690
but that was a good game.

23:58.130 --> 24:00.560
Master, I had a queen.

24:01.650 --> 24:03.920
That there queen of hearts.

24:04.120 --> 24:05.490
You think you did what?

24:05.690 --> 24:08.490
I played a queen of hearts.
I had it.

24:08.690 --> 24:10.450
Well, there's only one
queen of hearts in this deck.

24:10.650 --> 24:13.980
I had it, you saw it.

24:14.180 --> 24:15.540
Do you understand?

24:17.540 --> 24:19.540
You must not know
what a queen looks like.

24:23.150 --> 24:24.900
You cheated me.

24:25.100 --> 24:26.030
"Servants,

24:26.230 --> 24:27.510
obey in all things

24:27.710 --> 24:29.390
your masters
according to the flesh;

24:29.580 --> 24:32.480
not with eye service,
as men pleasers;

24:32.670 --> 24:35.000
but singleness of heart,
fearing God."

24:35.200 --> 24:39.530
"A false balance
is abomination to the Lord:

24:39.730 --> 24:41.090
but a just weight...

24:41.290 --> 24:43.440
- Silence your tongue, boy!
- ...is His delight!"

24:43.640 --> 24:44.650
[indistinct shouting]

24:46.480 --> 24:48.480
[grunting]

24:50.310 --> 24:51.410
You get your--

24:51.610 --> 24:52.960
[both shouting]

24:55.530 --> 24:57.190
You cheated me!

25:00.540 --> 25:02.550
[shouting]

25:02.750 --> 25:04.450
You cheated me!

25:25.520 --> 25:27.520
Bass, what you do?

25:31.660 --> 25:33.180
Bass?

25:34.010 --> 25:35.410
Are you hurt?

25:35.610 --> 25:37.060
I done messed up.

25:37.260 --> 25:39.140
For all of us.

25:41.880 --> 25:42.760
Oh, Lord.

25:42.960 --> 25:44.550
Bass, look at me.

25:44.750 --> 25:46.680
Look.

25:46.880 --> 25:48.770
You gonna run now.

25:48.970 --> 25:50.510
You gonna take a horse

25:50.710 --> 25:52.470
and you gonna run far from here,

25:52.670 --> 25:53.470
far from all this.

25:53.670 --> 25:54.510
- No--
- Yes,

25:54.710 --> 25:56.380
you are.

25:57.460 --> 25:59.470
I ain't watching you
get strung up and dead.

26:00.470 --> 26:01.560
I ain't.

26:01.760 --> 26:02.950
So you gonna run.

26:03.950 --> 26:05.690
You gonna run
and never look back.

26:06.690 --> 26:08.960
Promise me.

26:09.160 --> 26:10.920
I'm your woman. Do what I say.

26:11.120 --> 26:12.490
Promise me.

26:12.690 --> 26:14.660
<i>♪ quiet, dramatic music </i>

26:14.860 --> 26:16.570
<i>♪♪♪</i>

26:17.570 --> 26:18.960
I promise.

26:31.410 --> 26:32.550
I love you.

26:32.750 --> 26:33.990
I'm sorry.

26:34.190 --> 26:37.330
Don't ever look back.

26:41.810 --> 26:43.860
<i>♪♪♪</i>

27:09.710 --> 27:11.450
<i>♪♪♪</i>

27:30.990 --> 27:32.130
Gentlemen.

27:32.330 --> 27:33.740
Get off that damn horse.

27:33.940 --> 27:36.080
Yes, sir.

27:39.390 --> 27:41.140
[spits]

27:41.340 --> 27:42.480
Who's your master?

27:43.700 --> 27:46.220
Uh, George Reeves.

27:47.270 --> 27:49.310
He a major
in the 11th Texas Cavalry.

27:50.620 --> 27:52.110
I'll be.

27:52.310 --> 27:53.280
He important, ain't he?

27:53.480 --> 27:54.850
Yes, sir.

27:55.050 --> 27:57.060
So important he let
his niggers run loose?

27:58.190 --> 27:59.410
No, sir.

28:00.540 --> 28:02.630
I's headed to fetch his missus.

28:03.630 --> 28:05.420
She with kin in Sherman.

28:13.640 --> 28:14.780
[horse neighs]

28:14.980 --> 28:16.790
<i>♪ pulsing, dramatic music </i>

28:16.990 --> 28:19.390
<i>♪♪♪</i>

28:31.970 --> 28:33.710
<i>♪♪♪</i>

28:43.890 --> 28:46.630
<i>♪♪♪</i>

28:59.820 --> 29:01.480
[horse fussing]

29:01.680 --> 29:03.400
Come on, girl.

29:03.600 --> 29:06.270
[continues fussing]

29:06.470 --> 29:07.780
Okay, okay.

29:08.830 --> 29:11.800
- [whinnies]
- Okay.

29:12.000 --> 29:14.580
<i>♪ quiet, dramatic music </i>

29:14.780 --> 29:16.750
<i>♪♪♪</i>

29:20.800 --> 29:22.280
You're still a good girl.

29:24.060 --> 29:25.990
You're still a good girl.

29:26.190 --> 29:27.890
[distant dogs barking]

29:33.810 --> 29:35.780
<i>♪ pulsing, dramatic music </i>

29:35.980 --> 29:37.860
<i>♪♪♪</i>

30:19.250 --> 30:20.940
[grunts]

30:23.030 --> 30:25.090
<i>♪ quiet, dramatic music </i>

30:25.290 --> 30:27.180
<i>♪♪♪</i>

30:27.380 --> 30:29.300
[bird squawking]

30:39.400 --> 30:42.270
- [crunches]
- [grunts]

30:59.640 --> 31:01.380
<i>♪♪♪</i>

31:03.120 --> 31:05.080
[grunts]

31:14.220 --> 31:15.560
[gunshot]

31:38.330 --> 31:40.370
[insects trilling]

32:04.350 --> 32:05.660
[knife scraping]

32:10.400 --> 32:12.450
[birds chirping]

32:34.160 --> 32:35.650
<i>♪ dramatic string music </i>

32:35.850 --> 32:38.080
<i>♪♪♪</i>

32:52.490 --> 32:53.660
[cawing]

33:00.190 --> 33:02.450
[cawing]

33:04.370 --> 33:06.410
[flies buzzing]

33:08.330 --> 33:10.330
<i>♪♪♪</i>

33:30.830 --> 33:32.970
[rain pattering]

33:33.170 --> 33:35.620
[thunder rumbles]

33:45.280 --> 33:47.320
<i>♪♪♪</i>

33:56.860 --> 34:01.160
[singing quietly]

34:10.430 --> 34:12.130
[gunshot]

34:16.700 --> 34:18.090
Seminole?

34:19.880 --> 34:21.320
Runaway.

34:25.410 --> 34:27.070
<i>♪ quiet, dramatic music </i>

34:27.270 --> 34:29.190
<i>♪♪♪</i>

34:47.250 --> 34:48.600
Water.

34:52.690 --> 34:54.480
Water.

34:55.480 --> 34:57.180
[speaks Creek]

35:02.310 --> 35:04.320
Water.

35:04.520 --> 35:05.190
[speaks Creek]

35:30.210 --> 35:32.300
[speaks Creek]

35:48.710 --> 35:50.840
[chickens clucking]

35:54.930 --> 35:56.200
[goat bleating]

35:56.400 --> 35:59.060
[metal hammering]

36:04.370 --> 36:06.380
[sizzles]

36:21.300 --> 36:22.350
Thank you.

36:23.350 --> 36:25.220
You need rest.

36:30.530 --> 36:32.020
Where am I?

36:32.220 --> 36:33.930
Long way from anywhere.

36:37.890 --> 36:40.770
- I'm Sara.
- [metal clangs]

36:40.970 --> 36:44.340
This here is Pistol,
and you're troubling us both.

36:44.540 --> 36:45.760
[metal clanging]

36:47.290 --> 36:48.330
But you're home.

36:50.770 --> 36:52.380
For now.

36:55.990 --> 36:58.170
Thank you, Sara.

37:07.740 --> 37:09.440
This all yours?

37:10.920 --> 37:12.230
Me and my husband.

37:12.430 --> 37:14.660
Where he?

37:29.370 --> 37:31.900
- [door creaks]
- You cross the Red River?

37:34.420 --> 37:36.080
Escape the war?

37:36.280 --> 37:38.090
And the whip.

37:38.290 --> 37:41.130
Curtis don't know any of that.

37:41.330 --> 37:43.440
Nor I.

37:43.640 --> 37:45.300
Never felt the sting.

37:47.430 --> 37:49.310
But war, I do know.

37:51.260 --> 37:52.750
Fought in Florida to be free.

37:52.950 --> 37:54.280
<i>♪ somber, dramatic music </i>

37:54.480 --> 37:57.190
We Seminole never surrendered.

37:57.390 --> 37:59.270
Never made a worthless treaty.

38:00.620 --> 38:02.760
Now my people live here.

38:02.960 --> 38:05.150
Still free.

38:07.890 --> 38:10.460
My husband built us this home...

38:13.420 --> 38:15.300
...then died
in the white man's war,

38:15.500 --> 38:18.380
so Curtis never has
to wear chains.

38:24.510 --> 38:26.950
I left the woman I love.

38:33.520 --> 38:37.320
You can swing a hammer,
shoe a horse?

38:37.520 --> 38:40.490
I ain't afraid of work.

38:43.100 --> 38:45.410
You stay here.

38:45.610 --> 38:47.490
You help me and Curtis.

38:48.540 --> 38:50.190
You'll be free, too.

38:52.280 --> 38:54.020
[door creaks]

39:24.570 --> 39:25.920
In there?

39:33.890 --> 39:36.500
You want me to put my hand
in that hole? Where I can't see?

39:52.470 --> 39:54.820
- [shouts]
- [laughs]

39:59.040 --> 40:01.520
I don't need to speak Creek
to know you're poking fun.

40:03.570 --> 40:06.220
I think you know exactly
what I'm saying, too.

40:16.280 --> 40:18.320
[shouts]

40:20.280 --> 40:21.330
[gasps]

40:23.240 --> 40:25.380
<i>♪ uplifting music </i>

40:25.580 --> 40:27.420
<i>♪♪♪</i>

40:30.290 --> 40:31.420
[laughs]

40:45.390 --> 40:47.440
[laughs softly]

40:54.800 --> 40:56.680
<i>♪ somber, suspenseful music </i>

40:56.880 --> 40:58.580
<i>♪♪♪</i>

41:11.290 --> 41:13.730
[scoffs] Heed your call.

41:17.770 --> 41:18.730
[grunts]

42:06.820 --> 42:09.740
Any of you speak
a goddamn lick of English?

42:15.920 --> 42:18.540
John say there been
a run on goods lately,

42:18.740 --> 42:20.660
lot of folk coming and going.

42:21.800 --> 42:23.890
But he'd do it
for seven dollars.

42:24.090 --> 42:26.850
You two are slicker
than a slop jar.

42:27.050 --> 42:28.200
[money shuffling]

42:28.400 --> 42:30.200
I'll give you a quarter
to load it

42:30.400 --> 42:31.760
while me and my men eat lunch?

42:33.460 --> 42:37.720
A quarter for me,
a quarter for the boy.

42:42.470 --> 42:43.690
[sighs]

43:08.840 --> 43:11.410
[coughing]

43:19.810 --> 43:21.560
Romulus...

43:21.760 --> 43:23.340
and Remus.

43:23.540 --> 43:25.340
Both raised by wolves.

43:26.900 --> 43:28.000
Major Pierce.

43:28.200 --> 43:30.790
No "Major" now.

43:30.990 --> 43:32.300
Just Esau.

43:34.870 --> 43:36.040
This your boy?

43:38.870 --> 43:39.830
I won't bite.

43:45.180 --> 43:48.110
You prefer being a daddy to
putting daddies in the grave.

43:48.310 --> 43:49.890
The boy ain't mine.

43:50.090 --> 43:51.240
Could be, though.

43:51.440 --> 43:53.770
It's all there
for the taking now.

43:53.970 --> 43:55.890
Another man's cradle,
another man's bride.

43:57.190 --> 43:59.730
You returned to the wild, Bass.

43:59.930 --> 44:01.730
Freedom's a good color on you.

44:01.930 --> 44:03.780
I reckon it would be for anyone.

44:03.980 --> 44:05.780
Surprisingly, no.

44:05.980 --> 44:08.740
You'd think a man gifted freedom
would walk on his own accord,

44:08.940 --> 44:12.700
but... most prefer the comfort
of the master's leash

44:12.900 --> 44:15.740
to liberty and justice.

44:15.940 --> 44:18.830
If I was not in these irons,
I'd be happy to oblige them,

44:19.030 --> 44:20.350
Lincoln or no.

44:21.920 --> 44:23.270
Union won?

44:23.470 --> 44:26.140
Goddamn. No news here, I see.

44:27.490 --> 44:30.450
This faraway rock
you crawl under got a name?

44:30.650 --> 44:32.490
Turkey Creek.

44:34.490 --> 44:36.410
Well, gobble, gobble.

44:38.110 --> 44:39.900
[chains rattle]

44:40.100 --> 44:41.990
You best hurry up, Bass.

44:42.190 --> 44:45.030
Collect your whelp
and take flight.

44:45.230 --> 44:47.850
Hell is coming
on wings of its own.

44:52.160 --> 44:54.090
Curtis!

44:54.290 --> 44:56.780
- [people screaming]
- [gunfire]

44:58.870 --> 45:00.080
Now.

45:03.780 --> 45:05.180
[screaming]

45:11.970 --> 45:13.230
[Esau]
Find a gun!

45:24.280 --> 45:26.030
<i>♪ dramatic music </i>

45:26.230 --> 45:28.200
<i>♪♪♪</i>

45:30.110 --> 45:31.900
[high-pitched ringing]

45:36.990 --> 45:38.340
[breathing echoing]

45:49.090 --> 45:50.220
Stop.

45:54.400 --> 45:56.270
Your pup's got fangs.

46:00.320 --> 46:02.970
World wants both of us
breathing, boy.

46:04.150 --> 46:05.940
[Bass]
Curtis!

46:06.140 --> 46:07.030
No.

46:07.230 --> 46:09.150
You listen to your daddy now.

46:10.410 --> 46:11.850
Curtis!

46:13.980 --> 46:16.120
[shouts] No! No!

46:25.340 --> 46:26.790
[speaks Creek]

46:26.990 --> 46:29.780
Curtis. Curtis.
[speaks Creek]

46:31.090 --> 46:32.970
[screams]

46:33.170 --> 46:35.010
[speaking Creek]

46:35.210 --> 46:36.830
[panting]

46:38.360 --> 46:39.930
[screams]

46:40.130 --> 46:41.930
<i>♪ somber music </i>

46:42.130 --> 46:43.800
<i>♪♪♪</i>

47:06.210 --> 47:08.260
<i>♪♪♪</i>

47:18.130 --> 47:19.880
[insects trilling]

47:26.710 --> 47:29.020
He died brave.

47:30.410 --> 47:32.280
He lived brave.

47:37.500 --> 47:42.120
My loss... can't be yours.

47:45.160 --> 47:46.340
You take Pistol...

47:47.990 --> 47:49.960
...you live brave, too.

47:50.160 --> 47:52.000
<i>♪ somber, contemplative music </i>

47:52.200 --> 47:54.170
<i>♪♪♪</i>

47:56.650 --> 47:59.440
Your heart still beats.

48:15.020 --> 48:18.200
I hate to do this...

48:18.400 --> 48:21.070
but Miss Sara insisted.

48:22.460 --> 48:25.040
See, I made a promise
a long time ago

48:25.240 --> 48:26.900
I'm fixing to break.

48:30.820 --> 48:36.470
You be good to me, Pistol,
and I'll be good to you.

48:38.170 --> 48:39.910
That's all either of us can do.

48:48.530 --> 48:50.450
<i>♪ hopeful, sweeping music </i>

48:50.650 --> 48:53.140
<i>♪♪♪</i>

49:13.290 --> 49:15.570
<i>♪ quiet, contemplative music </i>

49:15.760 --> 49:17.730
<i>♪♪♪</i>

49:39.840 --> 49:42.150
<i>♪♪♪</i>

50:03.340 --> 50:05.390
<i>♪♪♪</i>

50:31.680 --> 50:33.720
<i>♪♪♪</i>

50:39.120 --> 50:40.600
[door creaks]

50:47.600 --> 50:49.750
That's a nice grey outside.

50:49.950 --> 50:52.660
Hard to miss it from the house.

50:52.860 --> 50:54.660
Mistress Rachel.

50:55.790 --> 50:58.280
I said you'd be back.

50:58.480 --> 51:02.500
George wouldn't believe it,
but I knew. I knew all along.

51:02.700 --> 51:05.110
- [exhales] Welcome home.
- I don't want no trouble.

51:05.310 --> 51:07.460
Have no fear, Bass.

51:07.660 --> 51:10.460
George isn't around,
and even if he was,

51:10.660 --> 51:13.110
you already beat the spit
and spite out of him.

51:14.410 --> 51:15.510
No...

51:15.710 --> 51:19.470
my husband's got his mind set
on politics.

51:19.670 --> 51:22.300
Fancies himself a legislator.

51:22.500 --> 51:25.220
As if that will allow him
to reclaim the things

51:25.420 --> 51:27.080
that were taken from us.

51:28.990 --> 51:30.650
The things?

51:31.820 --> 51:34.230
Or the people?

51:34.430 --> 51:37.350
We hold on something fierce
to what we love, don't we?

51:42.830 --> 51:45.500
Where'd Jennie go?

51:45.700 --> 51:47.660
[laughs softly]

51:55.460 --> 51:57.600
<i>♪ somber, contemplative music </i>

51:57.800 --> 51:59.330
<i>♪♪♪</i>

52:24.400 --> 52:26.440
<i>♪♪♪</i>

52:43.460 --> 52:45.900
- [Sally] Mama.
- Sally, dear.

52:46.980 --> 52:48.600
You're gonna be the death of me.

52:48.800 --> 52:49.990
[grunts]

52:55.430 --> 52:57.170
[babbles]

52:58.430 --> 53:00.170
<i>♪♪♪</i>

53:21.760 --> 53:23.800
[indistinct chatter]

53:52.880 --> 53:55.750
I hope he treats you right.

53:56.880 --> 53:58.580
What?

54:00.450 --> 54:02.550
Your new man.

54:02.750 --> 54:04.710
I hope he treats you right.

54:07.500 --> 54:09.550
He does.

54:11.550 --> 54:14.430
Got a bad habit of up
and disappearing, though.

54:14.630 --> 54:17.380
Too damn quiet at times.

54:18.340 --> 54:20.430
Stubborn as a mule.

54:21.430 --> 54:24.520
But that man sure does love
stubborn, too.

54:27.520 --> 54:29.570
He got a name?

54:30.780 --> 54:33.270
Bass.

54:33.470 --> 54:34.970
Bass Reeves.

54:35.170 --> 54:37.800
<i>♪ gentle music </i>

54:38.000 --> 54:39.970
<i>♪♪♪</i>

54:42.580 --> 54:45.370
Say hello...

54:45.570 --> 54:47.450
to your daughter.

54:50.590 --> 54:51.500
Hello.

54:56.510 --> 54:58.430
<i>♪ Father, Father </i>

54:58.630 --> 55:02.430
<i>♪ Let me love you </i>

55:02.630 --> 55:03.820
<i>♪ Let me </i>

55:08.690 --> 55:10.960
<i>♪ Father, Father </i>

55:11.160 --> 55:13.840
<i>♪ Let me love you </i>

55:14.040 --> 55:15.570
<i>♪ Let me </i>

55:18.880 --> 55:22.410
<i>♪ Saw you wandering in </i>

55:22.610 --> 55:25.800
<i>♪ My dream last night </i>

55:28.580 --> 55:31.550
<i>♪ Saw you wandering in </i>

55:31.750 --> 55:36.020
<i>♪ My dream last night </i>

55:40.850 --> 55:42.730
<i>♪ Father, Father </i>

55:42.930 --> 55:46.520
<i>♪ Let me know you </i>

55:46.720 --> 55:49.170
<i>♪ Let me</i>
<i>know you ♪</i>

55:53.690 --> 55:55.570
<i>♪ Father, Father </i>

55:55.770 --> 55:58.450
<i>♪ Let me know you </i>

55:58.650 --> 56:01.140
<i>♪ Let me show you </i>

56:09.010 --> 56:11.940
How many mouths you got to feed
with no harvest?

56:12.140 --> 56:14.030
What's your offer?

56:14.230 --> 56:15.510
<i>♪ exciting music </i>

56:15.710 --> 56:16.380
[Sherrill]
<i>Welcome to the Dead Line.</i>

56:16.580 --> 56:18.510
<i>Out here there ain't no laws.</i>

56:18.710 --> 56:20.420
- Only outlaws.
- Ready?

56:23.460 --> 56:24.340
Justice.

56:24.540 --> 56:26.040
<i>It's a dangerous job.</i>

56:26.240 --> 56:29.160
It's hard for a man to put fear
and hate behind him.

56:29.820 --> 56:32.390
You think you can handle
the weight of the badge?

56:32.590 --> 56:34.080
What'd you do?!

56:37.740 --> 56:39.620
<i>♪ atmospheric music </i>

56:39.820 --> 56:44.740
<i>♪♪♪</i>
